{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2faa7181-29f1-47b8-a7a3-be66f9c07037","content":"PID 12345 isn't running on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. Here's how to determine the runtime and configure dumps on **your** machine:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Detect CoreCLR vs NativeAOT\n\n```bash\n# If this returns matches → CoreCLR\ncat /proc/12345/maps | grep -E 'libcoreclr|libclrjit|libhostfxr'\n\n# If no matches → likely NativeAOT (single self-contained binary, no JIT)\n```\n\nYou can also check:\n```bash\nreadelf -p .comment /proc/12345/exe 2>/dev/null  # NativeAOT binaries have ILC markers\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2a. If **CoreCLR** — use built-in dump support\n\nSet these environment variables **before** launching the app:\n\n```bash\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1          # Enable automatic dumps on crash\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4            # 4 = Full heap dump (1=Mini, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=\"/tmp/coredumps/dump_%p_%t.dmp\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\nmkdir -p /tmp/coredumps\n```\n\nOr configure the **OS-level** core dump (works for both runtimes):\n\n```bash\n# Set core dump pattern\necho \"/tmp/coredumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nulimit -c unlimited   # Allow core dumps\nmkdir -p /tmp/coredumps\n```\n\n### 2b. If **NativeAOT** — use OS-level core dumps only\n\nNativeAOT does **not** support the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` variables. You must rely on the Linux kernel:\n\n```bash\n# Ensure core dumps are enabled\nulimit -c unlimited\necho \"/tmp/coredumps/core.%e.%p.%t\" | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nmkdir -p /tmp/coredumps\n```\n\nFor **systemd**-managed services, also set:\n```ini\n# In the [Service] section of your unit file\nLimitCORE=infinity\n```\n\nAnd if `systemd-coredump` is active:\n```bash\n# Check: coredumpctl list\n# Config: /etc/systemd/coredump.conf\n# Set Storage=external and ProcessSizeMax=8G (or suitable value)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick summary\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Detection** | `libcoreclr.so` in `/proc/PID/maps` | No CLR libs loaded |\n| **Best method** | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` | `kernel.core_pattern` + `ulimit -c unlimited` |\n| **Analysis tool** | `dotnet-dump analyze` | `gdb` / `lldb` |\n\nRun the detection command first, then apply the matching configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"621d716b-5724-49fc-b643-ea02e0458bf3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist on this machine. That's expected — the user is asking for guidance about a process on their own machine. Let me provide them with the diagnostic steps and configuration instructions.","outputTokens":837},"id":"7584c800-dbe0-4fb0-bc60-05d9c1d39364","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:00:07.595Z","parentId":"bf488389-1cc2-40c1-ae6f-621fc8585667"}
